      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false,
      "name": null,
      "patch_url": null
    },
    "body": "We don't use LTO in release builds, and neither do any of our dependencies, so disable support in GCC. This reduces what needs to be compiled when building the Guix toolchain. It would also make it clear if something started using it.\r\n\r\nAlso disable Native Language Support as this is also not needed:\r\n> The --enable-nls option enables Native Language Support (NLS), which lets GCC output diagnostics in languages other than American English. Native Language Support is enabled by default if not doing a canadian cross build.\r\n\r\nSee https://gcc.gnu.org/install/configure.html.",
